Some nights after King Haeo had arrived at Herlover, Ronald and Erling sailed out of the bay with their squadron. Ronald was separated from the rest at sea, and made for the Orlmeys with some of the ships. But Erling, and Andrew, and Halward steered south before the Shetland and so on to the west of 'Pharey- fiord, but saw no land except Sulna-stapa west of the Orkneys Afterwards they sailed in to Scotland under Dryness, and going into the country destroyed a castlo, but the garrison had fled. They also burned more than twenty hamlets. Asterwards etcer- ing for the Hebridos they found there Magnus king of Man.
